name: Five Stride Skate School - Bonnie Thunders and OMG WTF - Intermediate Blocking
description: Five Stride Skate School - Bonnie Thunders and OMG WTF - Intermediate Blocking 2:00pm to 5:00pm $50.00 Intermediate Blocking will cover all fundamentals of blocking including blocking specific agility, partner blocking in 2s, 3s, and 4s, and wall building. All participants will be required to wear protective tape on their knee guards, this will be supplied at check in. Class sizes will be restricted to 40 participants and open to female skaters only. *Tickets are restricted to one per person per session.* Sun State Roller Girls invite you to attend a series of Five Stride Skate School classes conducted by Bonnie Thunders and OMG WTF from Gotham Girls Roller Derby (GGRD), New York (NY). Bonnie Thunders Since the age of seven, Bonnie Thunders has spent her winters ice skating in pretty dresses and her summers pushing girls around on the soccer field. From 2002 through 2006, Bonnie competed at the US Figure Skating Association Synchronized Figure Skating Team National Championships with Syracuse University. Upon moving to New York City in 2006, she traded in her ice skates for roller skates and has been playing roller derby with GGRD ever since. As a member of the Bronx Gridlock, Bonnie has helped lead her team to 3 league championships. On the GGRD All Stars Bonnie has competed at the Women’s Flat Track Derby Association (WFTDA) Championship for five years, bringing home the title twice - the only team to do so in WFTDA history. Bonnie was MVP of the 2008 WFTDA Regional and National Championships and Derby News Network (DNN) Reader’s Poll Jammer of the Year in 2010 and 2011. Most recently, Bonnie competed at the Roller Derby World Cup as part of the Team USA who won first place. Bonnie actively competes on flat track and banked track roller derby. Off the track, Bonnie Thunders is the WFTDA Game Play Manager and co-owns Five Stride Skate Shop in Brooklyn, NY.

name: Five Stride Skate School - Bonnie Thunders and OMG WTF  - Advanced Blocking
description: Five Stride Skate School - Bonnie Thunders and OMG WTF - Advanced Blocking 18 February 2012 10:00am to 1:00pm $50.00 Advanced Blocking will also include partner blocking and wall building with a closer look at strategy and game play, thinking preemptively to create plays, backward blocking, and incorporating one on one blocking into team play. All participants will be required to wear protective tape on their knee guards, this will be supplied at check in.
